My game allows the user to double-tap to load the next game screen. With the latest MonoGame source a bug came out of nowhere: when I double-tap to skip to the next screen, a null reference error popped up:
(inside MonoGame.Framework/Graphics/RenderTarget2D.OpenGL.cs)

```
    protected override void Dispose(bool disposing)
    {
        if (!IsDisposed)
        {
            GraphicsDevice.AddDisposeAction(() => 
            {
                this.GraphicsDevice.PlatformDeleteRenderTarget(this);
            });
        }

        base.Dispose(disposing);
    }
```

The error shows that "this.GraphicsDevice" is null. 

My guess is that the reference to the GraphicsDevice of this RenderTarget2D has been cleared before calling this method. Thing were working properly with the MonoGame source back in September. Kind of wondering if there can be a quick fix to this issue... Thanks very much! =)
